        <abstract> 
<p>Very pleased at JSBS’s discovery ["On the electrical phenomena which accompany the contractions of the leaf of <hi rend="italic">Dionaea muscipula</hi>", <hi rend="italic">Rep. BAAS</hi> 43 (1873): 133].</p>  
<p>Asks for pure animal substances [proteins] for <hi rend="italic">Drosera</hi> experiments. His other sources have been T. L. Brunton, Edward Frankland, W. A. Miller (now dead), and Hoffmann of Berlin [A. W. von Hofmann?].</p> 
        </abstract>
